1
00:00:05,620 --> 00:00:08,240
Let's begin with self-introductions.

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,900
I'm Sonoko Saruhashi.

3
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:15,340
Um... nice to meet you all.

4
00:00:15,340 --> 00:00:18,140
Nice to meet you too.

5
00:00:18,140 --> 00:00:22,840
We only have one year left in
elementary school. Let's all get along.

6
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:24,240
Yeah!

7
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:28,720
Please take a seat at the
very back of this row.

8
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:32,000
What grade is everyone in?

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,080
Sixth grade.

10
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:35,580
Sono.

11
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:38,080
From today on, can I call you Sono?

12
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:42,420
I’m Emi Nakajima.
Call me Niko.

13
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,980
The always-smiling Niko!

14
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:47,420
- She’s always smiling.
- Nice to meet you.

15
00:00:48,180 --> 00:00:52,080
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

16
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,580
Good morning!

17
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:20,080
Good morning.

18
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:23,080
Niko.

19
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:26,080
- You like this?
- Yeah, I love it.

20
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,580
Look!

21
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,260
Me too!

22
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,080
Matching, right?

23
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:37,500
- Thank you, Jonouchi!
- Not at all!

24
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,440
- I’ve been wanting this!
- Right?

25
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:43,080
- Exactly! Look!
- That really suits you.

26
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:46,580
- Thank you for coming.
- You're welcome.

27
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:49,980
I'll take good care of this.

28
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:52,980
- I’ll be waiting in my room.
- Okay.

29
00:01:52,980 --> 00:01:55,080
Alright, see you later.

30
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:06,580
The smell of smoke still hangs
in the air around the scene.

31
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:13,580
The fire broke out on the sixth floor,
breaking windows and blackening walls.

32
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:24,080
Kanta Sakurai, 34, izakaya manager, was rescued
from the fire and is critically unconscious.

33
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:36,080
Around 40 fire trucks battled
the fierce fire for five hours, nearly burning the sixth floor.

34
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:41,080
- Flying in the sky.
- I hope that dream comes true.

35
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:43,580
My dream was to be a firefighter.

36
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:59,780
I understand how you feel, but without
his family's consent, you can't see him.

37
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,580
Excuse me.

38
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,600
Mr. Takaki.

39
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:11,160
Ah... from the police.

40
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:14,580
- To see Mr. Sakurai?
- Yes.

41
00:03:14,580 --> 00:03:18,580
I see... you were classmates, right?

42
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,580
We're in a tough spot.

43
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:33,960
We need to figure out if it was caused by
careless handling of fire, or something else entirely.

44
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:37,080
Arson, maybe...?

45
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:45,080
No, nothing like that was
found at the scene.

46
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,580
I see.

47
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,080
Well then.

48
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:02,000
They’re leaning toward
calling it an accident.

49
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,580
I see...

50
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:09,080
Something's off, right?

51
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:14,380
If they say it’s an accident,
then it’s an accident.

52
00:04:17,380 --> 00:04:21,240
I think we should start
with a grudge motive.

53
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,760
Grudge?

54
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:27,080
It means someone held a grudge.

55
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:37,740
This yearbook was hidden in a
time capsule unearthed after 22 years.

56
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:42,080
Six faces blacked out.
Their common link is...

57
00:04:44,580 --> 00:04:47,780
The six who bullied you.

58
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:49,400
Exactly.

59
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:56,080
First, Takeda, aka “Hin,”
fell to his death.

60
00:04:56,080 --> 00:05:02,580
Next, Sakurai, aka Kantaro, had a fire at
his izakaya and is still unconsious.

61
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:11,080
Police called it an accident, but
these two are being targeted over their future dreams.

62
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:18,580
If this is all part of a series of attacks,
there are four targets left.

63
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,800
You mean...

64
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:26,080
I looked into the classmates’
current status as much as possible.

65
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:33,940
Takahiro Koyama studies abroad
and runs a U.S. app development startup.

66
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:40,400
Since he lives in the U.S., we don’t know
how he’s involved in this case.

67
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:45,080
So that means he’s safe
as long as he’s oversaes.

68
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:51,080
His drawing was...

69
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,580
An astronaut, maybe?

70
00:05:55,580 --> 00:05:59,180
Getting killed in space?
That’s impossible.

71
00:05:59,180 --> 00:06:04,580
Hey, can you stop with that
simplistic thinking already?

72
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:06,580
Honestly, it's annoying.

73
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:11,240
- Sorry.
- Next.

74
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:17,940
Emi Nakajima modeled in her twenties but
retired without making it big.

75
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:22,580
Right now, she’s working as a hostess
at Roppongi’s club LUNVELLE.

76
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:28,580
She drew a picture of an idol.

77
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:34,580
An idol... Like getting hit
by the spotlight or something?

78
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:37,080
It’s possible that could be a weapon.

79
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:40,080
Taisuke Haryu.

80
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:48,080
He dropped out of Tokyo Tech University,
but I found no current information about him.

81
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,340
That’s a unique dream.

82
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:58,080
- Warrior?
- No... samurai.

83
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:01,040
I see.

84
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:06,080
And one of the remaining targets is...

85
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,580
"Sho Takaki"

86
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:11,220
You.

87
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:15,080
Let me see your drawing too.

88
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:38,200
What is this?

89
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,660
Hmm?

90
00:07:40,780 --> 00:07:43,580
- A hero...
- Huh? What?

91
00:07:43,580 --> 00:07:46,900
A hero.
I probably just drew it as a joke.

92
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,080
It’s just a childhood dream after all.

93
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:58,580
It’s reasonable to think
this crime is a revenge act for bullying against me.

94
00:07:58,580 --> 00:08:06,480
The culprit knows about the bullying I suffered and
was able to use the time capsule and drawings.

95
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,580
In other words,
it’s likely a classmate.

96
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:21,320
One of these people is
holding a grudge against you.

97
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:25,020
Someone other than me.

98
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:30,080
If you remember anything,
please tell me.

99
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:37,360
Yuki Tsuchiya, maiden name Yuki Hanawa,
housewife, and has a 13-year-old son.

100
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:41,080
Kengo Toyokawa, hairdresser.

101
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:46,580
He moved around various beauty salons in Tokyo
but seems to be working in Ginza now.

102
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:53,580
Saki Kobayashi, works at the local ward office
in Suginami. Couldn’t find any SNS account.

103
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:58,080
- Youjirou Tanaka...
- Wait a minute.

104
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,760
I can’t understand all this at once.

105
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,080
We were all just regular friends.

106
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:14,580
Before suspecting anyone,
shouldn’t we warn the three targeted they’re in danger?

107
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:21,080
I’ll also try contacting
the people I’m still connected to.

108
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:35,080
Got it. But don’t forget,
you’re also a target.

109
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,860
I know that.

110
00:09:57,520 --> 00:10:02,240
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

111
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:11,400
Hey boss, where’s the
stuff for the topcoat?

112
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,980
- Ah, it’s in the car.
- Got it.

113
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:18,320
“Your story could be a scoop!”

114
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,080
- Good morning.
- Morning.

115
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:40,920
Another day, another stair climb—
good job.

116
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:44,000
What’s wrong?
That bruise is huge!

117
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,600
Hmm.

118
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:52,780
- What’s this? Drugs?
- Yeah, it’s been popular lately.

119
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:57,740
We were close to the ringleader, but
the victim who tipped us off is gone.

120
00:11:57,740 --> 00:12:00,580
- Wow, tough luck.
- Ms. Shinonome... ouch!

121
00:12:00,580 --> 00:12:02,720
- Here!
- Mm?

122
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:08,700
This guy’s probably the ringleader.

123
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,080
Oh, thanks!

124
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:14,080
No testimony means
we need evidence.

125
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:24,080
When we get the evidence,
sushi’s on you.

126
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:28,080
Why are you telling me?
Get her to treat you.

127
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:33,000
Read the room, please.

128
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:36,500
- Look into this location.
- Okay.

129
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:40,760
“I got touch with Niko,
and we’re meeting tonight.”

130
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,860
Why here?

131
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:52,760
Can’t be helped.
It was specified.

132
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:03,380
- Hey.
- Spotlight…

133
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,420
King!

134
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:07,520
King.

135
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:19,280
Long time no see!

136
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:21,580
Long time no see.

137
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,520
Thanks for coming.

138
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:31,520
My boyfriend runs this place, and
I couldn’t miss the event today.

139
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:44,220
- Sorry for the short notice.
- I’m really happy to see you!

140
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:48,520
Sono, you’ve totally become famous!

141
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:52,020
You’ve always been beautiful, though.

142
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:56,020
How about you, King?
Did you take over the family business?

143
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:59,020
I wanted to go to the reunion too.

144
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:01,520
It overlapped with a golf tournament.

145
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:05,720
I’m pretty good at golf.
Don’t you play, King?

146
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,080
Well, yeah...

147
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,820
Um, can we change the place?

148
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:13,120
Niko, is that okay?

149
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,020
Ah! Oh, that!

150
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:18,140
I have one too. See?

151
00:14:18,140 --> 00:14:20,000
We’re matching.

152
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:27,520
Can we move somewhere else?
It’s noisy here.

153
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:32,520
You two seem a bit off.

154
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:37,020
It’s important.

155
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:42,720
I see...

156
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,680
You’re still mad, right?

157
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:52,840
Sono, I’m really sorry.

158
00:14:54,420 --> 00:15:00,740
I haven’t forgotten that I was mean to you
when we were in elementary school.

159
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:05,380
We were kids back then,
but still… I’m truly sorry.

160
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:11,540
Well, guys like King did it too,
so I was just caught up in the mood.

161
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:15,760
But it’s not like I hated you, Sono.

162
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:21,720
Now that we’ve finally reunited like this,
I want to get along.

163
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:25,520
I’m really sorry for back then.

164
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:29,520
Right?

165
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:37,020
You haven’t changed at all.

166
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,560
Niko.

167
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:42,520
We’re matching!

168
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:46,960
Sono.

169
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,040
Sorry...

170
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:58,020
This is my character... so
maybe it’s better if you take it off.

171
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:38,320
- Niko.
- What’s up?

172
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:40,020
Give me back.

173
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:43,320
Huh? Give back what?

174
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:46,880
Give me back my keychain!

175
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:51,020
That’s awful!
Are you saying I stole it?

176
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:56,020
But it was there.

177
00:16:56,020 --> 00:17:01,000
It was inside your desk.

178
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:05,360
So you looked inside
my desk without permission?

179
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:08,540
- Well...
- That’s the worst!

180
00:17:10,020 --> 00:17:13,400
Look, this is definitely mine.

181
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,020
Huh?

182
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:19,520
You lost it yourself,
so don’t go accusing others.

183
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:23,520
Apologize her.

184
00:17:30,180 --> 00:17:33,020
No way... I’m not in the wrong.

185
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:36,580
You treated my friend like a thief.

186
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:38,520
Apologize.

187
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,520
I’m sorry.

188
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:53,260
You really haven’t changed...

189
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:58,020
Don’t feel better just by apologizing.

190
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:02,320
You thought apologizing
would get you forgiven, huh?

191
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:06,020
Like, "I’m sorry for back then."
"No, it’s totally fine."

192
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:08,820
You’re so naive, really.

193
00:18:08,820 --> 00:18:11,520
No way I’m forgiving you.

194
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,780
Sono!

195
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:16,020
You said these were matching, right?

196
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:18,520
No, they’re not.

197
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:22,220
I bought this one myself.

198
00:18:22,220 --> 00:18:26,520
Don’t lump them together.
They’re totally different in value.

199
00:18:52,020 --> 00:18:53,740
Apologize.

200
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:55,520
I’m sorry.

201
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:01,140
Thief...!

202
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:07,520
- Whose backpack is this?
- Give it back.

203
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:31,520
This is such a pain!
What the heck was that?

204
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:35,520
It was more than 20 years ago.

205
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:42,520
No, we did something she can’t forget—
even after 20 years.

206
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:50,400
Hey, we’re changing locations, right?

207
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,560
Let’s go.

208
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:59,020
Niko, believe it or not… both Hin and Kantaro
were targeted because of these drawings.

209
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:03,720
- We could be next…
- Ah! Hey, you’re too good!

210
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,520
Usually, you’d go easy!

211
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:08,200
Sorry, we don’t do tab
or go easy here.

212
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:11,520
- Hey, Niko.
- King, you’re overthinking.

213
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:16,520
It’s sad about Hin and Kantaro.
Having accidents one after another like that...

214
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,880
They might not be accidents.

215
00:20:22,620 --> 00:20:24,920
Ugh, You interrupted again!

216
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:27,520
- That’s the game, huh?
- The worst.

217
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:30,680
Then next, I’d love a match with you.

218
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:34,520
What do you do for work?

219
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:37,520
Ah, well... just a
regular civil servant.

220
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,900
- Then never mind.
- What?

221
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:41,400
Too bad!

222
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:45,780
You got picked—
so smile and have fun!

223
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:48,220
I said it earlier,
now’s not the time.

224
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,520
Yeah, yeah.

225
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:52,240
Got picked?

226
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:54,680
Sometimes, they come to the lounge.

227
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:59,660
Like “Niko, long time no see!" —
classmates with obvious ulterior motives.

228
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,020
I don’t even remember them.

229
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:05,020
Do they really think now's their chance?

230
00:21:05,020 --> 00:21:10,520
But if it’s King, I wouldn’t mind meeting up.

231
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,340
Yeah...

232
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:15,020
- Super, super, super good.
- Shut up.

233
00:21:15,020 --> 00:21:17,900
Let’s fall in love! Wow wow...

234
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:21,020
Ouch, ouch!
Funny bone, funny bone!

235
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:23,260
Has he always been like this?

236
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:27,020
- Yeah, hasn’t changed at all.
- You’re still the same.

237
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:32,520
No, It’s not that.
I couldn’t change.

238
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:35,860
I had nothing.

239
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:46,020
I still put on a front even now and drink with men I dislike,
getting free brand stuff, smiling as Niko.

240
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:51,960
Super, super, super good?

241
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:55,520
Super, super good vibe?

242
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:58,580
So nostalgic!

243
00:21:58,580 --> 00:22:03,520
Hey, let’s sing a song!

244
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:06,020
Oh!

245
00:22:06,020 --> 00:22:08,380
I want to hear Niko sing!

246
00:22:08,380 --> 00:22:11,720
Life is wonderful.

247
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:18,460
Look, meeting someone, falling in love.

248
00:22:18,460 --> 00:22:21,020
Ah, wonderful!

249
00:22:21,020 --> 00:22:23,260
Ah, totally into it!

250
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:29,220
Being able to laugh and cry.

251
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:31,020
Yeah!

252
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,960
- That was awesome!
- Thanks!

253
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:38,020
Mr. Jonouchi!
Ah, sorry, sorry...

254
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:42,020
- Okay... thank you.
- Closing the door.

255
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:51,600
Found them, in the car.

256
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:55,860
Yeah, heading towards the main street...

257
00:22:55,860 --> 00:22:58,520
- Hey!
- You scared me!

258
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:02,860
- What are you doing?
- I was taking pictures of the birds.

259
00:23:02,860 --> 00:23:06,020
- There’re no birds.
- Seriously, there really were.

260
00:23:06,020 --> 00:23:08,520
- You took pictures of the car, right?
- I wasn’t.

261
00:23:10,020 --> 00:23:11,780
Birds... birds...

262
00:23:22,940 --> 00:23:25,700
“Weekly Apollo
Ken Matsui”

263
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:35,700
- What’s your aim?
- Sorry, I don’t get it...

264
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:39,160
Don’t play dumb.
Why are you following Niko?

265
00:23:41,780 --> 00:23:45,120
No idea, and even if I did,
I wouldn’t say.

266
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:47,840
You can’t forgive us, right?

267
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:51,840
- So you want to get a story...
- No, that’s not it!

268
00:24:01,020 --> 00:24:10,260
Of course… we can’t act like
what we did never happened.

269
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:19,460
But everyone’s doing their best to live.

270
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:24,960
Some forget, some don’t reflect...

271
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:27,940
They may not be good people,

272
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,000
but,,,

273
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:39,040
they struggle,
get hurt, and try to live.

274
00:24:47,140 --> 00:24:51,840
Probably doesn’t mean much
coming from me though...

275
00:24:59,980 --> 00:25:05,140
The person we were after
wasn’t Emi Nakajima.

276
00:25:05,140 --> 00:25:08,480
- It was her partner.
- Huh?

277
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:16,480
Please pretend you didn’t hear
what’s coming next.

278
00:25:19,780 --> 00:25:25,180
Emi Nakajima’s boyfriend is
suspected of dealing illegal drugs.

279
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:26,980
Illegal drugs?

280
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:33,300
Illegal synthetic drugs have been spreading
among youth in recent years.

281
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:42,480
People like them often link to organized crime.
We were tracking the ringleader, and by chance…

282
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:46,980
I don’t know about that person.
It’s just a coincidence.

283
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:53,480
So you really don’t know
anything about Niko’s involvement?

284
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:57,140
Oh, thanks!

285
00:25:57,140 --> 00:25:59,480
No testimony means
we need evidence.

286
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:04,980
- I don’t know.
- Really?

287
00:26:06,980 --> 00:26:08,500
Yes.

288
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:12,940
I’m really sorry.

289
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:16,600
It’s okay, but no sushi.

290
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:19,100
- What?!
- That’s quite a reaction!

291
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:21,100
- Come on, back to work.
- Okay.

292
00:26:23,580 --> 00:26:26,100
So, who was that guy?

293
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:28,600
Ah, uh...

294
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:33,500
A bully from the past.

295
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,480
I see.

296
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:37,640
A guy you can’t forgive...

297
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,820
He told me earlier,

298
00:26:41,820 --> 00:26:46,060
"What happened back then
can’t just be undone.”

299
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:49,920
I was the one who was bullied.

300
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:52,600
Well, that’s how it is.

301
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:56,840
What was done can’t be
erased for either side.

302
00:26:56,840 --> 00:27:00,780
They’ve carried that burden
their whole life.

303
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:04,220
So maybe it's okay not to forgive.

304
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:06,600
Yeah...

305
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:25,600
Life is wonderful.

306
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,600
Look, meeting someone...

307
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:32,600
Falling in love...

308
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:43,740
Hello, Mr. Jounouchi?

309
00:27:43,740 --> 00:27:46,600
Thank you for yesterday.

310
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:49,780
Now? Y-yes.

311
00:27:49,780 --> 00:27:52,100
Of course, that’s fine.

312
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:55,240
What…? I’m the one dancing?

313
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,860
Yeah, but it’s not the main part.

314
00:27:57,860 --> 00:28:02,240
One of the dancers dropped
out of tomorrow’s event.

315
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:06,600
Relax. You’re on the edge,
no one’s paying attentiion, Just dance.

316
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:12,260
- Yeah, right.
- Exactly.

317
00:28:13,300 --> 00:28:16,100
Huh? What’s that?

318
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:21,600
Funding source.

319
00:28:24,020 --> 00:28:27,980
So you’ll do it, right?
I’ll pay you, too.

320
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:30,600
Yes, of course.

321
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:55,940
Excuse me.

322
00:28:55,940 --> 00:29:00,900
Mr. Sakurai is still unconscious,
so visitations are prohibited.

323
00:29:00,900 --> 00:29:02,520
Ah, I see...

324
00:29:03,460 --> 00:29:05,600
I apologize for that.

325
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:09,460
- I’ll come again another time.
- Please.

326
00:29:17,500 --> 00:29:19,500
Niko, you’ve been requested.

327
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:21,000
Yes.

328
00:29:24,260 --> 00:29:27,000
- It’s Niko.
- Huh?

329
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:31,300
King? Huh? What, what…?
you came for me?

330
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:34,500
Oh, I’m so happy!
Thank you!

331
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:37,620
- Hey...
- What will you have? Whiskey okay?

332
00:29:37,620 --> 00:29:40,000
- Ah...
- Okay.

333
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:47,200
Well, I thought about calling,
but I figured it’s better to say it in person.

334
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:50,000
Huh? Why so formal?

335
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,000
- Your boyfriend...
- Yeah.

336
00:29:59,300 --> 00:30:02,000
Is he maybe involved in something bad?

337
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:07,000
Like drugs?

338
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:11,000
- You knew?
- Well, he does live pretty flashy.

339
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:15,520
- If that’s the case...
- Thanks for telling me.

340
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:23,680
But the bag and the apartment,
he gave me all of that.

341
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:27,500
I hate to admit it,
but Donoko’s right.

342
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:32,680
I’ve got nothing.

343
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:39,100
I can’t keep this job much longer,
and I can’t do without him.

344
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:44,000
- That’s not true.
- It actually is.

345
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:52,040
It’s not about good or bad anymore.
None of that matters.

346
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:58,500
It does matter, though.

347
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:04,240
The tabloids are onto it too.

348
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:08,500
If something about you
ends up in the tabloid…

349
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:12,500
Tabloid?
Is taht Donoko’s?

350
00:31:16,420 --> 00:31:18,960
I get it now.

351
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:23,340
- So it’s meant as revenge.
- It’s not like that...

352
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:28,340
She has surely made it on her own.

353
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:32,540
She’s strong.

354
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:37,660
Strong...

355
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,500
She tried to become strong.

356
00:31:48,060 --> 00:31:54,800
I get why you’d think what happened to
Hin and Kantaro was just an accident.

357
00:31:54,800 --> 00:32:02,000
But somehow...
I think maybe that's not the case.

358
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:07,200
So... please be careful.

359
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,580
Ritsu?

360
00:32:25,580 --> 00:32:28,300
Ah! It’s “R-E-2” — as in "Re2."

361
00:32:28,300 --> 00:32:31,500
The club in Yokohama, right?
I’m heading there now.

362
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:33,500
- Hey, Matsui.
- Yes?

363
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:36,680
- That was...
- From Ms. Shinonome.

364
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,740
That drug guy is holding
an event at the club.

365
00:32:39,740 --> 00:32:42,500
We might be able to catch him.

366
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:46,500
- I’m coming too.
- Huh?

367
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:48,500
Ah, okay...

368
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:10,360
“Shukan Apollo”

369
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:26,020
“No clinging to the past.
Cherish the present.”

370
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:30,200
“Sonoko Saruhashi”

371
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:33,040
Good morning!

372
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:36,380
Thief...!

373
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:42,000
You haven’t changed at all.

374
00:33:51,180 --> 00:33:55,500
- Why did you come?
- Hmm? I can’t leave bad guys alone.

375
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,180
As expected, right?

376
00:33:57,180 --> 00:34:01,000
- Idiot! She’s just kidding.
- Oh, really?

377
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,500
Whatever…

378
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:05,180
If something happens,
photograph it, okay?

379
00:34:05,180 --> 00:34:07,660
- Yes.
- Don’t get caught.

380
00:34:07,660 --> 00:34:09,560
I’ve got this.

381
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:55,000
Tonight’s special dancer, Velvet!

382
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,500
Yes?

383
00:35:45,500 --> 00:35:46,620
Yes.

384
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:50,940
I’m, uh... Koyama.

385
00:35:59,500 --> 00:36:00,500
Yo!

386
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:03,500
Tabo...

387
00:36:03,500 --> 00:36:05,500
Long time no see, King.

388
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:20,280
Did you find what you wanted?

389
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:23,460
- Shino...
- Thanks for your help.

390
00:36:23,460 --> 00:36:25,960
The rest is up to us.

391
00:36:28,740 --> 00:36:29,800
Yeah.

392
00:36:33,300 --> 00:36:34,940
Thanks.

393
00:36:39,340 --> 00:36:42,960
Wow, so nostalgic!
An astronaut.

394
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,720
You’re in the U.S. now, right?

395
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:53,220
Yeah, I started a company there.

396
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:54,840
Here.

397
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:57,760
I’ve been developing
games and apps.

398
00:36:57,760 --> 00:36:59,460
Other things too.

399
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:01,440
"CEO"...

400
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:05,620
A CEO in the U.S… wow.

401
00:37:05,620 --> 00:37:08,740
You’re the same, right?
You took over the family biz?

402
00:37:08,740 --> 00:37:12,500
Well... yeah...

403
00:37:12,500 --> 00:37:15,440
So, when did you come back to Japan?

404
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:18,380
- Just recently.
- Why?

405
00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:20,960
I had a press conference
for a new business.

406
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,960
So I came back to Japan for
the first time in a while.

407
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:28,140
Then I got a call from Kantaro

408
00:37:28,140 --> 00:37:33,380
and heard everything about the
yearbook and the reunion.

409
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:35,960
I see...

410
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:40,460
I can’t believe
what happened to Hin...

411
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,340
Yeah...

412
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:52,960
One day Hin…

413
00:37:54,460 --> 00:37:57,520
In the forest Kantaro…

414
00:37:57,520 --> 00:38:00,440
A bear and Niko…

415
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:03,960
Met Tabo…

416
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:08,820
A forest path in bloom with Chonmage…

417
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:13,640
A bear met Taka-King!

418
00:38:14,740 --> 00:38:16,240
What was that again?

419
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:20,160
You don’t remember? My parody song.
We used to sing it all the time.

420
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:22,960
Oh... I kinda remember that.

421
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:27,100
I guess we’ll never
sing it together again…

422
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:32,960
That’s sad…

423
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:36,600
Yeah...

424
00:38:40,420 --> 00:38:42,460
Well then, I guess I…

425
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:47,640
I might get killed in space.

426
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:50,300
- That’s not funny…
- You should be careful too.

427
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:52,160
You’re not alone anymore.

428
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,640
Let’s grab a bite next time
we’ve got some free time.

429
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:58,460
Talk about old times and all.

430
00:38:58,460 --> 00:39:00,460
See you.

431
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,780
Donoko.

432
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:24,460
You were at that club, right?

433
00:39:24,460 --> 00:39:26,980
- Did you follow me?
- Yeah.

434
00:39:26,980 --> 00:39:30,460
I heard from King that
the tabloids are after us.

435
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:36,140
- What is it?
- Nothing.

436
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:39,460
I just thought
your frown never changes.

437
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:44,960
You always made that face
when things weren’t going well.

438
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:47,460
Are you here to mock me?

439
00:39:47,460 --> 00:39:51,400
You want this, right?

440
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,460
Here, take this.

441
00:39:57,140 --> 00:39:59,960
There’s data in here.

442
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:08,160
Here.

443
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:10,180
Why?

444
00:40:10,180 --> 00:40:14,960
- Because it’s profitable, isn’t it?
- No, I mean why this?

445
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:18,060
The other day, I apologized, right?

446
00:40:18,060 --> 00:40:20,960
- That was a lie.
- Huh?

447
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,960
The truth is, I don’t feel bad.

448
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:29,460
It was over 20 years ago, so
honestly I don’t remember well.

449
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:33,460
So I can’t sincerely apologize.

450
00:40:33,460 --> 00:40:35,960
But you sure remember it well.

451
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:40,460
You’re persistent, or rather, stubborn.

452
00:40:40,460 --> 00:40:44,460
- That’s because of you...
- But...

453
00:40:44,460 --> 00:40:47,460
That’s why you were able to change.

454
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:51,300
I couldn’t change.

455
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:55,480
I couldn’t make an effort.

456
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:59,960
So slowly, slowly, everything’s
been going downhill.

457
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:05,460
I wonder where I went wrong.

458
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:09,460
There are so many things
I want to do over.

459
00:41:09,460 --> 00:41:12,460
Seriously, it pisses me off.

460
00:41:14,460 --> 00:41:16,460
So, well...

461
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:28,340
I can’t apologize for all, but this is a
replacement for the keychain I took.

462
00:41:28,340 --> 00:41:30,960
THE DOG.

463
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,000
Yes, that one.

464
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:37,960
THE DOG, huh... nostalgic.

465
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:49,460
So, punish those bad guys for me.

466
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:57,960
Leave it to me.

467
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:07,960
Who do you think you are?

468
00:42:18,060 --> 00:42:20,440
One day Hin…

469
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:22,960
In the forest Kantaro…

470
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:25,460
A bear and Niko…

471
00:42:25,460 --> 00:42:27,460
Met Ta…

472
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,960
One Hin

473
00:42:37,460 --> 00:42:39,960
Forest Kantaro

474
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:42,960
A bear...

475
00:42:50,060 --> 00:42:51,920
“Sho Takaki”

476
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:56,460
Hello, this is Saruhashi.

477
00:42:56,460 --> 00:43:00,260
- Next target is Niko.
- Huh? What do you mean?

478
00:43:00,260 --> 00:43:04,300
It might be in the same order
as the parody song we used to sing.

479
00:43:04,300 --> 00:43:06,840
- What are you talking about?
- Just find Niko!

480
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,460
Ah, wait...

481
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:18,960
Life is

482
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:22,040
Wonderful.

483
00:43:23,460 --> 00:43:27,960
Look, just like always.

484
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:49,460
It’s the same path.

485
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:53,960
Let’s find something!

486
00:43:56,960 --> 00:44:01,960
Ah, wonderful.

487
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:05,960
Ah, meeting someone.

488
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:11,960
A path to encounter someone.
